What is Bandwidth Overage Protection?
<phrase key="FaqQuestion17Text" />
Bandwidth Overage Protection guards you from overage charges by automatically suspending your account when you exceed the allowed bandwidth for your plan. To reinstate your server, simply purchase additional bandwidth, or wait until the start of the next billing cycle.
Bandwidth Overage Protection cannot be added to an account when it is already over its allotted bandwidth.
If you donât already have Bandwidth Overage Protection, and an overage occurs, you can suspend your account manually or purchase additional bandwidth to get you through until the next billing cycle.
For more information, see <a href="javascript:atl_PopUp('[@T[link:<external linktype='communityurl' path='help/article/1418/' secure='false'><param name='isc' value='gtnila43' /><param name='ci' value='90961' /></external>]@T]','display2','left=20,top=20,scrollbars=yes,resizable=yes,width=800,height=700');" >How Do I Add Bandwidth Overage Protection to My Account?</a>
